content.description: Start at the right edge of the white Quartz looking Arete left of "Black Crack". Crack. Climb the arete to easier finish.
content.protection: Will need to be creative to run TR. A good length of Static line (for distant trees) can be essential.

content.description: Start on up the right side wall on easy horizontal edges, follow the edge of the huge chimney that splits Illusion and Illusion Right as it begins to overhang. Pull through a few hard moves to gain the overhang, then finish directly above the chimney in a prominent crack.
content.protection: cams/tricams, nuts, from fingers to hands. Anchor from trees 20-30ft from cliff edge or with small to large gear in the crack atop the route.
content.location: Right of Illusion, on the right side wall of the chimney separating the South End cliff in two.

content.protection: Great gear. Static line may be needed for TR.

content.description: Fun, quick route for more creative gear placement than Black Hole Sun. Short route with good ledges for new trad climbers. For top roping, can set up a gear anchor or use short ropes to get to the trees.
content.protection: Good gear placement on horizontals at regular intervals
content.location: Immediately right of the crack with the tree

content.description: Same start as Black Hole Sun. Traverse left to right at the wider overhang about 5' to about the midpoint between the arete and start. Crux move here to pull up to easier climbing.
content.protection: Cams & Stoppers. Static line can come in handy when setting TR.
content.location: Start on a ledge about 5' up, 20' left of White Arete

content.description: Variation of white arete just off to the right, but not quite into black crack.  There's a solid path straight up if you never go around the side of the arete.
content.protection: Set up toprope with natural anchors, not much room in the way of gear placement mid-route
content.location: Start approx 3 feet to the left of black crack and move straight up.  Try not to move too far to the left or right as you'll cross into black crack or white arete respectively.

content.description: I doubt I'm the first person to do this route (the start holds had chalk on them), but It hasn't been posted on here yet. Set your hands, step your feet up, and dyno up to a jug on the overhang. Pull the roof and continue up the face (5.7). This is really a one move wonder with a V2-3 start move.
content.protection: Could be trad climbed but there is no gear for the start move. Best to TR.
content.location: Start on a ledge under the roof just left of White Arete. Start on a sharp right finger pocket and a left hand crimp.

content.description: Climb Cynosure but go straight up to roof instead of off to left to meet "Black Crack".
content.protection:
Lead: Sm to MD cams. Tricams and Nuts if you're creative.  

  TR: You may need to be creative to run TR. A good length of Static line (for distant trees) can be essential.

content.description: Pump through the steep face to the right of "Black Crack" then join back up with the route at the end.
content.protection:
Lead: Sm to MD cams.  LG cams for anchor. Great placements on solid rock. 

  TR: You may need to be creative to run TR. A good length of Static line (for distant trees) can be essential.
content.location: Steep face to right of "Black Crack".

content.description: Climb up into the small roof and pull over the larger roof from left to right. Continue easier climbing to the top. Pull the small roof at the top for some added fun.
content.protection: Good gear all the way. Good route for beginning leaders.
content.location: Start on a ledge about 5' up, 20' left of White Arete, left of the roof.

content.description: Big positive holds to the top. Would be a good first lead.
content.protection: Easily top anchor setup off trees.
content.location: Route is just to the left of Black Hole Sun. Coming in from the top, look for an open lip to the right of the Black Crack/White Arete boulders.

content.description: Southernmost outcropping on the cliff band.  The Black Crack (5.9) is an area favorite.
